[normal]sheet in the year-end 2012. That is a requirement on us to increase our capital on a go-forward basis. At that time, certainly by March 2013, we had announced our intention to sell our general insurance business and we were already in the process of completing the transaction to sell our life and savings business. The capital from both those transactions was to be redeployed into the bank
[normal],
[normal] and that was intended to offset the deteriorating capital base because of the non-core business.
